.TH ZOS-CLONE-CHECK 1 "February 2026" "zOS-clone 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zos-clone-check \- validate COBOL syntax
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zos-clone check
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse and validate COBOL source code without generating any output files.
This is useful for syntax checking and identifying errors before compilation.
.PP
The checker performs lexical analysis, parsing, and semantic analysis to
identify issues such as:
.IP \(bu 2
Syntax errors
.IP \(bu 2
Undefined identifiers
.IP \(bu 2
Type mismatches
.IP \(bu 2
Invalid COBOL constructs
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-I ", " \-\-include " " \fIDIR\fR
Additional copybook search paths. Can be specified multiple times.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
No errors found.
.TP
.B 1
Syntax or semantic errors detected.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check a COBOL file:
.B zos-clone check program.cbl
.TP
Check with copybook paths:
.B zos-clone check program.cbl -I ./copybooks
